CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 20, 1957, pg. 9, reads: "Student Boss - Alvin Francis, a senior at McKeespoort High School, talks with his shop teacher, Mr. Nelson. Alvin exchanged places with Mr. Nelson during the Turn About Day program at the school, and became the teacher.  This type of student-teacher exchange was done throughout the school. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Student Alvin Francis talking to shop teacher Mr. Nelson in McKeesport High School during "Turn About Day,"  McKeesport
